The paper deals with the problem of rendezvous of mobile agents in a network, which is a topic in multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The agents operate in an undirected graph with edge weights, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the communication complexity of achieving rendezvous, which is a topic in networking (cs.NI). Finally, the paper proposes algorithms for solving the rendezvous problem, which involves optimization and decision-making, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
